        "text": "One, if not the, central distinction of systems theory is that of consciousness and social system. When one refers to social systems, one refers in this theory to a field free of consciousness; when one refers to consciousness, one refers to a field free of sociality. This does not mean at all that social systems can be thought of without consciousness in their environment, or that consciousness can come about without contact with social systems at all; but it does mean that the social system is not"
